<subSubSection id="11D265234547B645B595FC9CFE201E83" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="597736A84547B645B595FC9CFE201E83" blockId="4.[151,1436,704,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4547B645B595FC9CFE801E5B" bold="true" box="[199,317,777,803]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">Remarks:</emphasis>
Reported as an endemic of the Crimea and originally described from the plain and foothill part of the peninsula by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594547B645B47CFCB9FE501E3F" author="Pliginsky, V." box="[302,493,812,839]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" pagination="363 - 367" refId="ref16559" refString="Pliginsky, V. (1914) Novye vidy roda Boreus Latr. iz Kryma (Neuroptera, Panorpidae). [The new species of the genus Boreus Latr. from Crimea (Neuroptera, Panorpidae]. Russkoe Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 14, 363 - 367. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1914">Pliginsky (1914)</bibRefCitation>
. Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594547B645B713FCB8FCB31E3F" author="Martynova, O. M." box="[577,782,812,839]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" pagination="54 - 66" refId="ref15638" refString="Martynova, O. M. (1954) Skopionnitsy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR. I [Scorpion-flies (Mecoptera) of USSR fauna. I]. Trudy Zoologicheskogo instituta Akademii nauk SSSR, 15, 54 - 66. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1954">Martynova (1954)</bibRefCitation>
studied most of the 
<typeStatus id="8673880A4547B645B6A7FCB8FB981E3F" box="[1013,1061,813,839]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4547B645B1C1FCB8FAFB1E3E" authorityName="Pliginsky" authorityYear="1914" box="[1171,1350,812,838]" class="Insecta" family="Boreidae" genus="Boreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chadzhigireji">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4547B645B1C1FCB8FAFB1E3E" box="[1171,1350,812,838]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">B. chadzhigireji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
housed in the collection of ZIN RAS (former ZIN 
<collectingCountry id="21DF76384547B645B7DCFCC4FD0F1E13" box="[654,690,849,875]" name="American Samoa" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">AS</collectingCountry>
USSR) and drew conclusions about the similarity of all species described from Crimea. Nevertheless, the author refrained from bringing all names into synonymy because of the absence of the 
<typeStatus id="8673880A4547B645B46DFC0CFED21ECB" box="[319,367,921,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4547B645B489FC0CFDFE1ECA" authorityName="Pliginski" authorityYear="1914" box="[475,579,921,946]" class="Insecta" family="Boreidae" genus="Boreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navasi">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4547B645B489FC0CFDFE1ECA" box="[475,579,921,946]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">B. navasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4547B645B728FC0CFD561ECA" authorityName="Pliginsky" authorityYear="1914" box="[634,747,920,946]" class="Insecta" family="Boreidae" genus="Boreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aktijari">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4547B645B728FC0CFD561ECA" box="[634,747,920,946]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">B. aktijari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594547B645B7ABFC0DFC0F1ECB" author="Nikolaev, G. V." box="[761,946,920,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" pagination="195 - 197" refId="ref16200" refString="Nikolaev, G. V. (2015) Problemy izucheniya skorpionovykh mukh roda Boreus Latreille, 1816 (Mecoptera: Boreidae) v Rossii. [Problems of studying of snow scorpion-flies of the genus Boreus Latreille, 1816 (Mecoptera: Boreidae) in Russia]. Scientific proceedings of the State Natural Reserve &quot; Prisurskii &quot;, 30 (1), 195 - 197. [in Russian, English summary]" type="journal article" year="2015">Nikolaev (2015)</bibRefCitation>
suggested the possibility of the distribution of the species also in the Caucasus, and considered 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4547B645B784FC28FC831EAE" authorityName="Pliginski" authorityYear="1914" box="[726,830,957,982]" class="Insecta" family="Boreidae" genus="Boreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navasi">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4547B645B784FC28FC831EAE" box="[726,830,957,982]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">B. navasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4547B645B626FC28FC581EAE" authorityName="Pliginsky" authorityYear="1914" box="[884,997,956,982]" class="Insecta" family="Boreidae" genus="Boreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aktijari">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4547B645B626FC28FC581EAE" box="[884,997,956,982]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">B. aktijari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B4547B645B1B9FC28FA211EAE" authorityName="Pliginsky" authorityYear="1914" box="[1259,1436,956,982]" class="Insecta" family="Boreidae" genus="Boreus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chadzhigireji">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA4547B645B1B9FC28FA211EAE" box="[1259,1436,956,982]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="463">B. chadzhigireji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594547B645B5CDFC75FEF41E83" author="Nikolaev, G. V." box="[159,329,992,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" pagination="239 - 248" refId="ref16151" refString="Nikolaev, G. V. (2003) Skorpionovye mukhi semeistva Boreidae (Mecoptera) Azii. [Snow scorpion-flies of the family Boreidae (Mecoptera) of Asia]. Tethys entomological research, 8, 239 - 248. [in Russian, English summary]" type="journal article" year="2003">Nikolaev 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B594547B645B406FC75FE2C1E83" author="Nikolaev, G. V." box="[340,401,992,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="463" pagination="195 - 197" refId="ref16200" refString="Nikolaev, G. V. (2015) Problemy izucheniya skorpionovykh mukh roda Boreus Latreille, 1816 (Mecoptera: Boreidae) v Rossii. [Problems of studying of snow scorpion-flies of the genus Boreus Latreille, 1816 (Mecoptera: Boreidae) in Russia]. Scientific proceedings of the State Natural Reserve &quot; Prisurskii &quot;, 30 (1), 195 - 197. [in Russian, English summary]" type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
